main event: An object was picked up on ground radar in Indian Springs, Nevada, on September 20, 1960.
interesting points: The radar return was solid, strong, and constant for a duration of 1.5 minutes., The object was not picked up on any other radar sets., It remained at a constant altitude and did not change speed or direction during the observation., Several other sightings had been reported in the area in the months leading up to this report., A retired captain reported observing 10-15 flying disc-shaped objects in the Las Vegas area shortly before this sighting.
witness description: no visual or audible sightings reported
